On the 24 of February, 2018, Innovation 22, a personal finance and lifestyle platform for young professionals and entrepreneurs held a networking and panel session that touched the challenges and triumphs millennials face while trying to grow their careers and/or business and also trying to balance finding the right partner or making time for their existing relationships. The event which took place on Saturday, February 24 at Workstation, No 7, Ibiyinka Olorunbe Close, Victoria Island Lagos from 2 PM to 5 PM had six panellists that talked about everything from careers to romantic relationships. Read More: FirstBank  sponsors 2018 Social Media Week The event ended with a networking session among the attendees. See the images from the event. Read More: Black Rules At BAFTAs 2018 Read More: Nigerian athletes upbeat ahead Warri/Efurun ‘peace’ marathon